  "texts": [
    "We introduce some notation to make the proofs of Theorems 1 and 2 easier to read.",
    "Bold letters (such as B or µ) are used to represent vectors and matrices.",
    "Any vector by default is a column vector.",
    "For a matrix B, the j-th row is denoted by (B) j•, and the (i, i ′)-th entry is denoted by B ii ′.",
    "Moreover, ∥B∥ F denotes the Frobenius norm of the matrix B."
